aspguidp.controller.input.element

Class EntityInputController

  • java.lang.Object
    • aspguidp.controller.input.element.InputElementController
      • aspguidp.controller.input.element.EntityInputController
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Depends_onEntityInputController, TaskEntityInputController

    public abstract class EntityInputController
extends InputElementController
    Base controller class for an entity input component. This class implements functionality which is used by all entity input components of the application.

      • initializeInputFieldAutocompletePopup

        protected void initializeInputFieldAutocompletePopup(DataServicePool dataServicePool,
                                                     javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField)
        Initialize an autocomplete popup for the given input field with the given data service pool.

        This method creates a new suggestion service for the display template parts of the given service pool and initializes an autocomplete popup with this suggestion service. Additionally, the autocomplete popup is initialized in such a way, that suggestions are excluded, if they are already displayed in the list view of the entity input component.

        Parameters:
        dataServicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to initialize the autocomplete popup for the given input field
        inputField - input field for which the autocomplete popup is initialized

      • initializeInputFieldKeyPressHandler

        protected void initializeInputFieldKeyPressHandler(javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField,
                                                   javafx.scene.control.Button inputButton)
        Initialize a key pressed handler for the given input field, which fires the given input button on an enter key event if the button is not disabled and which traverses the focus to the next input element on an tab key event.
        Parameters:
        inputField - input field on which the handler is set up
        inputButton - input button which is fired on enter key press if it is not disabled

      • initializeInputFieldValidation

        protected void initializeInputFieldValidation(DataServicePool servicePool,
                                              javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField,
                                              javafx.scene.control.TextField backgroundField)
        Initialize the validation of the given stacked field (which consists of an input field and a background field) of the entity input component with the given service pool.

        This method creates a new validation service for the display template parts of the given service pool and sets up a handler which sets the respective css class to the given background field on text change of the given input field. Additionally, this method creates a new suggestion service for the template parts of the given service pool and sets the prompt text of the given background field to the prompt text which is gathered from this suggestion service on text change of the input field.

        Parameters:
        servicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to initialize the validation of the given input field
        inputField - input field of the stacked field of which the validation which is initialized
        backgroundField - background field of the stacked field of which the validation which is initialized

      • initializeInputButton

        protected void initializeInputButton(DataServicePool servicePool,
                                     javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField,
                                     javafx.scene.control.TextField backgroundField,
                                     javafx.scene.control.Button inputButton)
        Initialize the input button of the entity input component with the given service pool and the given stacked field (which consists of an input field and a background field).

        This method sets up a handler which disables the input button, when the given background field signals that it is not validated as valid. Additionally, a handler is set up, which adds the input of the given input field to the entity data manager of the service pool, when the button is clicked.

        Parameters:
        servicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to initialize the input button
        inputField - input field of which the value is added to the entity data manager of the given service pool
        backgroundField - background field which of which the validation status checked
        inputButton - input button which is initialized

      • initializeListViewCountLabel

        protected void initializeListViewCountLabel(DataServicePool servicePool,
                                            javafx.scene.control.Label countLabel,
                                            int minCount,
                                            int maxCount)
        Initialize the given list view count label of the entity input component with the given service pool and the given min and max entity counts.

        This method binds the text of the given count label to the count of entities which are displayed in the list view of the entity input component. Additionally, a handler is set up which sets a validation invalid class, if the count of entities displayed in the list view contradicts the given min and max entity count.

        Parameters:
        servicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to initialize the given count label
        countLabel - count label which is initialized
        minCount - minimum valid count of entities for the list view
        maxCount - maximum valid count of entities for the list view

      • initializeListView

        protected void initializeListView(DataServicePool dataServicePool,
                                  javafx.scene.control.ListView<Entity> entityList)
        Initialize the given list view of an entity input component with the given service pool.

        This method sets the items of the given list to the entities of the entity data manger of the given service pool. The list is set up to display the entities in an alphabetically ascending order. The value factory of the given list view is set up to use removable list cells. Additionally, a handler is initialized, which removes the currently selected items from the list when the del key is pressed.

        Parameters:
        dataServicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to initialize the list view
        entityList - list view which is initialized

      • registerInputElementStatus

        protected void registerInputElementStatus(DataServicePool dataServicePool,
                                          int inputCountMin,
                                          int inputCountMax)
        Register the execution status and the data status of the entity component to the execution/data service manager of the application.

        The execution status of an entity input component is set to true, if the count of entities managed by the data manager of the given service pool fulfills the given min and max entity counts. The data status of an entity input component is set to true, if the entity data manager of the given service pool holds at least one entity.

        Parameters:
        dataServicePool - service pool which holds the data services which are used to determine the execution/data status of the entity input component
        inputCountMin - minimum valid count of entities of the entity input component
        inputCountMax - maximum valid count of entities of the entity input component
